#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/wavelet_decompose.rst:18
msgid "Wavelet decompose uses wavelet scales to turn the current layer into a set of layers with each holding a different type of pattern that is visible within the image. This is used in texture and pattern making to remove unwanted noise quickly from a texture."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/wavelet_decompose.rst:20
msgid "You can find it under :menuselection:`Image`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/wavelet_decompose.rst:22
msgid "When you select it, it will ask for the amount of wavelet scales. More scales, more different layers. Press :guilabel:`OK`, and it will generate a group layer containing the layers with their proper blending modes:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/filters/wavelet_decompose.rst:27
msgid "Adjust a given layer with middle gray to neutralize it, and merge everything with the :guilabel:`Grain Merge` blending mode to merge it into the end image properly."
msgstr ""

